<p>F 7 Sun<br/>Hot. Dopey day.<br/>Play with the cricket Ball all night &amp; enjoy myself immensely. Send photo of Southampton &amp; of Room &amp; [indecipherable]  &amp; of  myself at Eastleigh.<br/>Wrote Mum</p>
<p>F 8 Mon<br/>Very hot but lovely at night.<br/>Poor May goes away &amp; Siddie  &amp;  I play cricket  &amp;  have supper with Top.<br/>Wrote Dad. Mum 6  &amp; George.</p>
<p>W 9 Tues.<br/>Heavy Rain Storms etc.<br/>Read all night &amp; go to bed at 9.15 am in daylight. First time all Summer with one exception.<br/>Draw up new standing orders.</p>
<p>W 10 Wed<br/>Heavy Rain Storms &amp; Hail.<br/>Get organised &amp; dressed to go to Picton<br/>Go with T. Park. Paint Hall E &amp; I all around Beacon Hill in bush walk.<br/>Wrote Roy. Norm. Bess &amp; Aunt Annie</p>
<p>W 11 Th<br/>Torrential Rains. Joe is [indecipherable] &amp; sleeps in our Room. Write all night. Col. Goes on leave.  Ellis goes playing [whist?] its keen.<br/>Wrote M.R.L<br/>Wrote Doris. Maisie. Carter. Peg. Cyril. Bert</p>
<p>W 12 Fri<br/>Recd Socks, Chocs  &amp;  Cigs from Maisie Carter. Rains like Babylon &amp;  I stay in room &amp; read all night.<br/>T.B. Wright   &amp; I play with cricket ball &amp; we get sore hands T &amp;  I go for our  &amp; [rall?] wicket</p>
<p>W 13 Sat<br/>&amp;Fine. Go to Sarum at 2 pm. Go to 13 &amp; close [ice?]. Have nice time &amp;  dinner at YM &amp; Osmonds.<br/>Ride home in 45 minutes. Go all over old Sarum it is a wonderful place.</p>
